				<section id="sec-2">
				<p>Apart from the Indices Eurostat and the NSOs offer a list of almost 200 commodities with nominal prices. It is far from the abilities of both Producer and Consumer Indices to facilitate market behavior comparisons because a/ its scope is very limited – 197 commodities against 728 goods and services in the Consumer Price Index b/ to compare nominal prices is a complicated process, the price of a commodity means different thing in every given National Market and to compare markets this differences have to be calculated in the price.</p><br>
				</br><p>But nevertheless the set of nominal prices can be very useful for Regional and Local Markets. Even for an experienced person it will be difficult to build a Price Index for, let’s say, Pork Leg at the Local Market for the last five years. But with a reach variety of prices at 28 European Markets it will be easier to account for a normal or abnormal behavior of the Pork Leg in Milano.</p><br>
